Label: source
Description: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

Label: administered to
Description: Indicates that a treatment or substance is administered to a patient or organism.

Label: affects (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of an effect relationship.

Label: associated with (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of statistical or observed association.

Label: augments (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that an entity enhances or augments another.

Label: causes (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of a causal relationship between entities.

Label: coexists with (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that conditions tend to occur together.

Label: complicates
Description: Indicates that one condition complicates or worsens another condition.

Label: converts to
Description: Indicates a biochemical conversion or transformation.

Label: diagnoses (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that a test or procedure diagnoses a condition.

Label: disrupts (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of disruption or interference.

Label: inhibits (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that an entity inhibits another entity or process.

Label: interacts with (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of physical or functional interaction.

Label: is a (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of type or classification relationships.

Label: location of (specific)
Description: Indicates a specific anatomical or cellular location.

Label: manifestation of (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of manifestation relationships.

Label: measurement of
Description: Indicates what entity or property is being measured.

Label: measures
Description: Indicates that a test or assay measures a specific entity or quantity.

Label: method of
Description: Indicates that something is a method or approach for achieving a goal.

Label: administered to (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding administration.

Label: affects (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding effects.

Label: associated with (negative evidence)
Description: Negative or contradictory evidence regarding association.

Label: augments (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding augmentation.

Label: causes (negative evidence)
Description: Negative or contradictory evidence regarding causation.

Label: coexists with (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding co-occurrence.

Label: complicates (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding complication relationships.

Label: converts to (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding conversion.

Label: diagnoses (negative evidence)
Description: Negative or contradictory evidence regarding diagnostic capability.

Label: disrupts (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding disruption.

Label: inhibits (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding inhibition.

Label: interacts with (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding interactions.

Label: is a (negative evidence)

Label: location of (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding location.

Label: manifestation of (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding manifestations.

Label: measurement of (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding what is measured.

Label: measures (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding measurement capability.

Label: method of (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding methodological relationships.

Description: Negative evidence regarding part-whole relationships.

Label: predisposes (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding predisposition.

Label: prevents (negative evidence)

Description: Negative evidence regarding process relationships.

Label: produces (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding production.

Label: stimulates (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding stimulation.

Label: treats (negative evidence)
Description: Negative or contradictory evidence regarding treatment effectiveness.

Label: uses (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding usage.

Label: higher than (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding comparative magnitude.

Label: lower than (negative evidence)
Description: Negative evidence regarding comparative magnitude.

Label: occurs in
Description: Indicates that a process or phenomenon occurs in a specific context or location.

Label: part of (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of a part-whole relationship.

Label: precedes (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of temporal precedence.

Label: predisposes (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence of predisposition or increased risk.

Label: prevents (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that an entity prevents a disease or condition.

Label: process of
Description: Indicates that a process is associated with or part of another entity.

Label: produces
Description: Indicates that an entity produces or generates another entity.

Label: stimulates
Description: Indicates that an entity stimulates or activates another entity or process.

Label: treats (positive evidence)
Description: Positive evidence that a substance or procedure treats a disease or condition.

Label: uses
Description: Indicates that a procedure or process uses a specific entity or method.

Label: compared with
Description: Indicates entities being compared in a study or analysis.

Label: higher than
Description: Indicates that a measurement or value is higher than another.

Label: lower than
Description: Indicates that a measurement or value is lower than another.

Label: same as
Description: Indicates entity equivalence or identity.

Label: Entity
Description: The root class for all entities in the Biolink Model, representing any biological, chemical, or clinical entity.

Label: affects
Description: Indicates that an entity has an effect on another entity.

Label: associated with
Description: Indicates a statistical or observed association between entities.

Label: category
Description: The category or type classification of an entity in the Biolink model.

Label: causes
Description: Indicates that an entity is a causal agent for a disease, phenotype, or biological process.

Label: coexists with
Description: Indicates that two entities tend to occur together.

Label: decreases amount or activity of
Description: Indicates that an entity decreases the quantity or activity level of another entity.

Label: diagnoses
Description: Indicates that a procedure or test is used to diagnose a disease or condition.

Label: disrupts
Description: Indicates that an entity disrupts or interferes with the normal function of another entity.

Label: increases amount or activity of
Description: Indicates that an entity increases the quantity or activity level of another entity.

Label: interacts with
Description: Indicates a physical or functional interaction between entities.

Label: location of
Description: Indicates the anatomical or cellular location where an entity is found or a process occurs.

Label: manifestation of
Description: Indicates that a phenotype or symptom is a manifestation of a disease or condition.

Label: part of
Description: Indicates that one entity is a component or part of another entity.

Label: precedes
Description: Indicates that one biological process or event occurs before another.

Label: predisposes to condition
Description: Indicates that an entity increases susceptibility to or risk of a condition.

Label: preventative for condition
Description: Indicates that an intervention or treatment is preventative for a specific condition.

Label: prevents
Description: Indicates that an entity prevents or reduces the likelihood of a disease or condition.

Label: subclass of
Description: Indicates a hierarchical relationship where one class is a more specific type of another.

Label: treats
Description: Indicates that a substance or procedure treats or is therapeutic for a disease or condition.
